Cage is a F with a past medical history of hypertension who presented 3d after an episode of central heavy aching pain in her chest while she was carrying groceries.

Utterances.UttText: She reports that she felt faint and like her "breath had been taken away".
She denied sweating, LOC, or palpitations during the episode.
The pain dissipated after she rested for 5-10 minutes.
She reports 2-3 similar episodes in the last 4 months while she was climbing stairs and chasing after the bus.

Utterances.UttText: She describes these episodes as feeling a 'twinge'.
She also reports a 1 one year history of pressure in her upper abdomen after she eats a "big meal".

Utterances.UttText: She reports that she will feel the pain 1-2x a week and it always disappears after 3-5 minutes.
